<div class="slider-wrapper"><div class="slider-panel"><div class="workshop-step"><section><h2 id="0">Before you begin</h2><p>This Codelab teaches you how to create a <a href="https://shopify.dev/themes/architecture/sections">section</a> for an existing Shopify theme. For this Codelab we will be building a countdown section. This is an often used feature that is provided by <a href="https://apps.shopify.com/search?q=countdown">many apps on our store</a>, but can actually be implemented as a section as well.</p><p><img src="/content/images/themes-timer-section/timer-running-editor.gif" alt="Timer running in editor"/></p><aside class="callout callout-positive border-green-500 bg-green-50 rounded-md border-l-4  p-4"><dt>Positive</dt><dd>Throughout this Codelab you will find links to our documentation. This is not required reading to progress through this Codelab - it should be a self-contained experience. However, feel free to check them out if you should get stuck or simply want to dive deeper into a topic.</dd></aside><h3>Prerequisites</h3><p>Basic experience in HTML, CSS and Javascript are required for this Codelab.
Some experience with <a href="https://shopify.dev/api/liquid">Liquid</a> (the language in which Shopify templates are written in) is helpful but certainly not mandatory.</p><h3>Learning objectives</h3><ul>
<li>Use your local development environment for working on themes</li>
<li>Add a custom section to existing themes</li>
<li>Make section configurable via settings in the theme editor</li>
</ul><h3>What you&#x27;ll need (Shopify Account Requirements)</h3><ul>
<li>If you don’t have one, <a href="https://partners.shopify.com/signup">create a Shopify partner account</a>.</li>
<li>If you don’t have one, <a href="https://help.shopify.com/en/partners/dashboard/development-stores#create-a-development-store">create a Development store</a> where you can install and test your theme.</li>
</ul><h3>What you&#x27;ll need (Libraries and Tools)</h3><ul>
<li>You have installed <a href="https://nodejs.org/en/download/">Node.js</a> which is required to ...</li>
<li>... install the <a href="https://shopify.dev/themes/tools/cli/install">Shopify CLI</a>.</li>
</ul></section></div></div><div class="slider-controls"><button class="slider-control btn btn-small btn-tertiary-outline prev shadow-md invisible" disabled="">Back</button><button class="slider-control btn btn-small btn-tertiary next shadow-md ">Next</button></div></div></div></main><script>((STORAGE_KEY, restoreKey) => {
